## The situation

Fade House is a premium barbershop at 142 E Main St in Spartanburg, SC. Owner Marcus Johnson has been cutting hair for over 8 years and opened the shop in 2024 with a clear vision: an upscale, modern barbershop experience — good music, complimentary drinks, professional consultation before every cut.

The reputation was strong. 180 Google reviews with a 4.9-star average. A growing TikTok presence with cut transformation videos. Four barbers with full chairs most days.

But the business was running on Instagram DMs and walk-ins. And it was costing them.

## The problems

- **No-shows**: With no deposits and no formal booking, customers would commit via DM and not show up. That's $300-500 in lost chair time every month.
- **50+ daily DMs**: "What are your hours?" "How much for a fade?" "Is Marcus available Saturday?" The same questions, over and over. Manual replies eating into cutting time.
- **No online visibility**: People searching "barbershop Spartanburg" or "barber near me" found competitors first — including a new shop that opened two blocks away.
- **No barber selection**: Customers couldn't see which barber specializes in what, or check individual availability before showing up.

## What we built

### Online booking with deposits

Every barber has their own booking page with real-time availability. Customers pick their barber, choose a time, and pay a $10 refundable deposit through Stripe. Cancel with 2 hours notice and the deposit is returned. Don't show up? The shop keeps it.

The result: no-shows dropped immediately. When money is on the line, people show up.

### AI chat assistant

A floating chat button on every page answers the questions Marcus used to handle 50+ times daily:

- "What are your hours?" → Instant answer
- "How much for a beard sculpt?" → Full pricing breakdown
- "Is anyone available this afternoon?" → Checks real availability
- "What's the difference between a fade and a taper?" → Detailed explanation

It doesn't replace Marcus — it handles the repetitive questions so Marcus can focus on cutting.

### Barber profiles

Each barber gets their own page: photo, specialties, years of experience, and a direct booking link. Customers who want a specific barber can find them and book in seconds. Customers who don't care can browse all barbers and pick based on availability.

### Gallery

The best cuts, fades, and beard work — pulled from the shop's portfolio. This is the sales pitch for a barbershop. New customers scroll the gallery, see the quality, and book.

### Premium design

Dark background, gold accents. The website feels like walking into the shop — confident, clean, premium. Not a generic template. Mobile-first, because that's how 90% of barbershop searches happen.

## The results

- **Online booking live**: Customers book and pay deposits from their phone
- **No-shows reduced**: Deposit system changed behavior immediately
- **AI handling questions**: 50+ daily DMs reduced to a handful that need personal attention
- **Google visibility**: Optimized for "barbershop Spartanburg" with BarberShop schema markup
- **4 barber profiles**: Each barber manages their own schedule and specialties

Visit the site: [fade-house-barbershop.pages.dev](https://fade-house-barbershop.pages.dev)

## Why this matters for your business

If you run a service business — salon, spa, gym, studio — and you're managing appointments through DMs or phone calls, you're leaving money on the table. Online booking with a small deposit changes the game. And an AI assistant that handles the repetitive questions frees you up to do what you actually do best.

